de.wwu.muggl.vm.impl.symbolic
Class SymbolicVirtualMachine

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Thread
      de.wwu.muggl.vm.VirtualMachine
          de.wwu.muggl.vm.impl.symbolic.SymbolicVirtualMachine
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Runnable
Direct Known Subclasses:
LogicVirtualMachine
public class SymbolicVirtualMachine
extends VirtualMachine

This concrete class represents a virtual machine for the symbolic execution of java bytecode, especially focusing on the generation of test cases. It inherits methods from the abstract implementation, providing additional methods as well as overriding others.

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-08-29
Author:
Tim Majchrzak

SymbolicVirtualMachine

public SymbolicVirtualMachine(SearchAlgorithm searchAlgorithm,
                              SymbolicVirtualMachine succeededSVM)
                       throws InitializationException
Special constructor, which sets the search algorithm and initializes the other fields. It is used to start a "fresh" symbolic virtual machine during execution and start from scratch. The virtual machine specified is succeeded by it. The solutions found in the earlier execution and old statistical records are imported. If also the measuring of execution time is enabled, the old execution times are imported.

Parameters:
searchAlgorithm - The search algorithm used.
succeededSVM - The SymbolicalVirtualMachine that is succeeded by this one.
Throws:
InitializationException - If initialization of auxiliary classes fails.
java.lang.NullPointerException - If succeededSVM is null.
Method Detail

runMainLoop

protected void runMainLoop(Frame visualStartingFrame)
                    throws ExecutionException,
                           java.lang.InterruptedException,
                           InvalidInstructionInitialisationException
The main loop on the SymbolicalVirtualMachine executes the VirtualMachines main loop; it then saves the found solutions, checks weather a tracking back is possible and continues from that point on, again using the normal VirtualMachines main loop. It keeps doing so, until tracking back is no longer possible.

Overrides:
runMainLoop in class VirtualMachine
Parameters:
visualStartingFrame - If step by step execution is enabled, there will be no stepping until this frame has been reached.
Throws:
ExecutionException - An ExecutionExeption is thrown on any fatal errors during execution.
java.lang.InterruptedException - Thrown to signal the manual end of the step by step execution.
InvalidInstructionInitialisationException - Any fatal problems with the parsing and the initialization will lead to this exception.
java.lang.OutOfMemoryError - If the virtual machine runs out for memory, this error is thrown.
java.lang.StackOverflowError - If the operand stack of a frame or the virtual machine stack exceeds its element limit, this Error is thrown.

generateNewChoicePoint

public void generateNewChoicePoint(Switch instruction,
                                   de.wwu.testtool.expressions.Term termFromStack,
                                   de.wwu.testtool.expressions.IntConstant[] keys,
                                   int[] pcs,
                                   de.wwu.testtool.expressions.IntConstant low,
                                   de.wwu.testtool.expressions.IntConstant high)
                            throws SymbolicExecutionException
Generate a new choice point.

Parameters:
instruction - The Instruction generating the ChoicePoint.
termFromStack - The term term that was on top of the stack. Using the non symbolic execution, this would be the key for the switch.
keys - The possible keys.
pcs - The possible jump targets.
low - The "low" boundary of the tableswitch instruction; or null, if the choice point is generated for a lookupswitch instruction.
high - The "high" boundary of the tableswitch instruction; or null, if the choice point is generated for a lookupswitch instruction.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the number of keys is not equal to the number of jump targets or if there are no choices at all.
java.lang.NullPointerException - If either of the specified arrays is null, or if the instruction is tableswitch and at least one of the boundaries is null.
SymbolicExecutionException - If an Exception is thrown during the choice point generation.

getExecutionTimeInformation

public long[] getExecutionTimeInformation()
Return an array of long elements with the times of the execution measurement. If it is disabled, an array of zero length will be returned. The array has six entries: 0 - Time spent on the execution of instructions. 1 - Time spent on the detection of loops. 2 - Time spent on the coverage checking. 3 - Time spent on the generation of choice points. 4 - Time spent on the solving of constraints. 5 - Time spent on backtracking. 6 - Time spent on the generation of solutions. The time spent on the execution of instructions has already been reduced by the time spent on the generation of choice points (including solving), which is a sub task. The time is in milliseconds and can directly be used for displaying issues.

Returns:
An array of long elements with the times of the execution measurement.
